<li id="cite_note-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8" title="">^</a></b> * <cite id="Reference-Fredrickson.2C_Tugade.2C_Waugh.2C_.26_Larkin.2C_-200e">Fredrickson, B. L., Tugade, M. M., Waugh, C. E., &amp; Larkin, G.. R. (2003). <a href="http://web.ebscohost.com.ezproxy1.lib.ou.edu/ehost/pdf?vid=4&amp;hid=5&amp;sid=f030e481-0e36-422c-8f50-475601c1d35a%40sessionmgr9" class="external text" title="http://web.ebscohost.com.ezproxy1.lib.ou.edu/ehost/pdf?vid=4&amp;hid=5&amp;sid=f030e481-0e36-422c-8f50-475601c1d35a%40sessionmgr9" rel="nofollow">" A prospective study of resilience and emotions following the terrorist attacks on the United States on September 11th, 2002.</a> <i>Journal of Personality and Social Psychology, 84(2),</i> 365-376.</cite></li>
<li id="cite_note-9"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9" title="">^</a></b> <cite id="Reference-Luthar.2C_-1999">Luthar, S. S. (1999). <i>Poverty and children’s adjustment.</i></cite> Newbury Park, CA: Sage</li>
<li id="cite_note-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10" title="">^</a></b> <cite id="Reference-Luthar.2C_-1999">Luthar, S. S. (1999). <i>Poverty and children’s adjustment.</i></cite> Newbury Park, CA: Sage</li>
